HEADWORD: Fatiscence
<hw>Fa*tis"cence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fatiscense</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>fatiscere</ets> to gape or crack
open.]</ety> <def>A gaping or opening; state of being chinky, or having
apertures.</def> <rj><au>Kirwan.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

